tal in dollar assets and hedge these exposures through foreign exchange (FX=
) derivatives. As the dollar appreciated in March 2020, ICPFs sold large qu=
antities of gilts to meet margin calls on their short-dollar derivative pos=
itions, contributing to the yield spike in the gilt market. ...</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">UK insurers held nearly =C2=A3250 billion of dollar de=
nominated assets in their portfolios at the end of 2019, which equals rough=
