und sterling at the end of the contract). The magnitude of these hedges is =
substantial: our analyses show that insurers initiate a hedge of nearly 50 =
cents for every dollar of US$ exposure, on average.</p><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">During the Covid crisis, however, investors were in desperate need=
